title: Anything You Can Do...
creator: Randall Garrett
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: An alien crash lands on Earth, and for ten years terrorizes the planet, hiding, periodically killing and eating people and stealing materials for some unknown purpose. The only hope is Bart Stanton, a medically-engineered superman, designed for the sole purpose of confronting the “Nipe”. (Summary by Mark Nelson) Narrated by Mark Nelson For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org . M4B format available
subject: aliens; science fiction;genetic engineering;space;

reviews.reviewbody:
An alien lands on Earth, and it is so powerful, it can kill with very little effort. It also eats its victims, piling up the bones in ritualistic fashion. It sounds like a savage beast, but things are not always as it seems.

I found this to be an unusual story, but I am not sure if I liked it or not. The reader was excellent, and so were the quality of the recordings.
